edu.uncc.cs.bridges

Class AbstractVertex<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.uncc.cs.bridges.AbstractVertex<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<AbstractVertex<T>>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BSTNode, DLListNode, QueueElement, StackElement, Vertex

    public abstract class AbstractVertex<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<AbstractVertex<T>>
    Base class for visual graph vertices; either subclass it or use Vertex. Implement `outgoing` with any List-compatible structure to get different performance characteristics. The default implementation Vertex uses a HashMap. You are free to use any you prefer.
